If the Air Traffic Control folks are hiring... how about releasing a game that simulates the different control towers? Ie, partner with a brand that IS already in that space... oh.. I don't know... maybe Microsoft's Flight Simulator? Which already has tie ins to real life flight systems? Or the Open Flight Simulator out there which likewise has realtime data feeds?

So much better approaches to recruiting and making the role appealing. But instead... this shows just how old school the space still is... if the knee jerk reaction is to go to a marketing department to come up with an advertisement... that isn't fully thought out... -_-;;

